[Student "W"]
{[showcards W:HA E:HQ S:H5 N:H6]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \HA, East puts on the \HQ. It's your play. 

Play the \H2.

East's \HQ is either a singleton, (practically impossible), or a signal showing that he also holds the \HJ. In either case you can reach the East hand on the second trick by playing a low \H. Since you don't particularly want to start playing \Ds from your side, you go ahead and play a small \H, won by East with the \HJ.

East next plays the \DQ and however South tries it your side will take the next two \D tricks and set the contract.}
[Play "W"]HA

